*Hugs* <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujannellesilverthorne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jannelle Silverthorne</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ashborne Member</span><br>   <font color=#000000>(8/26/00 8:59:54 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=Http://home.san.rr.com/ashborne/Members/Jannellesmall.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Guild invitation</span><hr size=1> Rosey,<br>
<br>
I apologize for not explaining our normal looting policy better at the time in Karnor. I probably also confused the issue when I had mentioned that I was still looking for some Flayed Skin armor, which no one in the group could use personally.<br>
<br>
I understand your concern and think that it was just a lack of communication on my part that caused the issue in the first place.<br>
<br>
The way I prefer to handle loot is by need of the characters in the group at the time. Characters who are there and would use the item as more than a backup piece of gear get first priority.<br>
<br>
Lacking anyone who needs it in the group, I then like to consider planes level alternates of the current group as they could be brought along to a raid depending on the needs of the day.<br>
<br>
Then comes guild/alliance primaries who could use the item on a regular basis especially if it's a class defining item. Ex. My Silver Swiftblade which came from Mcruff et al.<br>
<br>
Lastly and for more mundane items that no one wants for use it is lotto among the group. Ex. The last few pieces of Flayed Skin armor that I'm helping a non-alliance friend obtain. If it drops in a group I'm in, I'll either lotto, or agree to buy it from the group.<br>
<br>
This is just a loose guideline and discussion among the group is always the final authority. In pickup groups, I do not expect them to follow all of my own guidelines. I express my opinion that an item usable by someone in the group who also desires the item should go to them. Any random loot is lotto to be disposed of by the winner as they see fit. <p>Tunare bless,<br>
Jannelle Alcedonia (Karana)<br>
Ashborne<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ureprobus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reprobus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ashborne Member</span><br>   <font color=#000000>(8/26/00 12:59:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Guild invitation</span><hr size=1> No worries Rosey, this is why we require potential members to spend time with us before being considered for membership. So they can get a feel for the way we handle things within the guild. Don't expect any overnight decisions tho. The time spent getting familiar with the guild is necessary on both the guild side and prospective members side. An invitation is only issued when the invitee is practically part of the family anyways. We've done it this way since day one, and it is the primary reason we are the best guild in Norrath. In this time u may decide that Ashborne is not the guild for u. <br>
<br>
I hope it's not discouraging, but we don't offer invites to people simply because they need a guild and are friends with a number of people within the guild. If we did we would be much larger, and probably vulnerable to the same fates of many other guilds that have spun out of control.<br>
<br>
Most of us can tell u that gaining membership takes time. I spent 2 or 3 months playing alongside the good people of Danse Macabre (Ashborne pre-merger) before that fateful night in the Frenzied Ghoul's slimy murky layer when Vyktor offered my medding ass membership.<br>
<br>
I realized just how much better the game had gotten for me, both in my enjoyment of it and my performance as a wiz, during those months. I learned more about fighting as a group than i had ever learned in my first 30 levels. And was lucky enough to be doing it with the kewlest and most skillful players i ever met.<br>
<br>
And in the time before i actually got the invite, the sense of urgency to join had faded. Playing alongside them was a rewarding enough experience. A game that had grown rather stagnant, was more fun than ever when i hooked up with these folk. I had been friends with Utrie and Denaiya for some time, but an invitation isn't offered upon a recommendation. It's offered when it becomes a technicality. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Last night was a blast by the way. =) Thanks for putting up with me while i played with aoes. =)<br>
<br>
Repro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bdansemacabre.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rosey>Rosey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#000000>(8/26/00 8:51:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Guild invitation</span><hr size=1> Rep hun, <br>
